{"word":"G4624 - σκανδαλίζω - skandalízō - skan-dal-id'-zo - Offend","slug":"G4624","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">σκανδαλίζω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>skandalízō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>skan-dal-id'-zo"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Offend"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C3;&#x03BA;&#x03B1;&#x03BD;&#x03B4;&#x03B1;&#x03BB;&#x03B9;&#x0301;&#x03B6;&#x03C9; - skandalizo&#x0304;</b> - <i>skan-dal-id'-zo</i><p/>To &ldquo;scandalize&rdquo;; from <a href=\"#/G4625\">G4625</a>; to <i>entrap</i>, that is, <i>trip</i> up (figuratively <i>stumble</i> [transitively] or <i>entice</i> to sin, apostasy or displeasure): - (make to) offend."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G4625\">G4625</a>"}]}